From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 23:30:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] ws2_32: Avoid dereferencing a missing connect address.

The wine-staging AF_UNIX support reads the address family before the
address has been checked.  Killing Floor 3's PROS SDK uses a zero-length
connect request while entering the main menu, so the staging code crashes
instead of allowing the request to reach AFD as it did previously.

Only inspect the address when the caller supplied enough data for the
AF_UNIX path, and avoid passing a NULL pointer to memcpy for a zero-length
request.  Preserve the previous AFD behavior for the SDK's NULL, zero-length
request while still rejecting a missing nonempty address.
---
 dlls/ws2_32/socket.c | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/ws2_32/socket.c b/dlls/ws2_32/socket.c
index 89cc9f7f5c8..188c2869a3b 100644
--- a/dlls/ws2_32/socket.c
+++ b/dlls/ws2_32/socket.c
@@ -1337,9 +1337,15 @@ int WINAPI connect( SOCKET s, const struct sockaddr *addr, int len )
 
     TRACE( "socket %#Ix, addr %s, len %d\n", s, debugstr_sockaddr(addr), len );
 
+    if (!addr && len)
+    {
+        SetLastError( WSAEFAULT );
+        return -1;
+    }
+
     if (!(sync_event = get_sync_event())) return -1;
 
-    if (addr->sa_family == AF_UNIX && *addr->sa_data)
+    if (addr && len > (int)offsetof(struct sockaddr_un, sun_path) && addr->sa_family == AF_UNIX && *addr->sa_data)
     {
         WCHAR *sun_pathW = strdupAtoW(addr->sa_data);
         unix_path = wine_get_unix_file_name(sun_pathW);
@@ -1356,7 +1361,8 @@ int WINAPI connect( SOCKET s, const struct sockaddr *addr, int len )
     }
     params->addr_len = len;
     params->synchronous = TRUE;
-    memcpy( params + 1, addr, len );
+    if (len)
+        memcpy( params + 1, addr, len );
     if (unix_path)
         memcpy( (char *)(params + 1) + len, unix_path, unix_varargs_size );
 
-- 
